<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-research-and-innovation> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "UK Research and Innovation (UKRI) is the national funding agency investing in science and research in the UK. Operating across the whole of the UK with a combined budget of more than £6 billion, UKRI brings together the 7 Research Councils, Innovate UK and Research England. UKRI is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Science, Innovation and Technology ."@en .
